Title: How to Invest Your Time to Achieve Success with Jenna Kutcher
Description:
Join us as our host, George Kamel, talks to Jenna Kutcher. Jenna is an entrepreneur, a bestselling author and the host of The Goal Digger Podcast. She shares why continually taking on more work can be a pitfall for leaders and gives you a way to say no while being tactful and kind. She also provides a helpful practice she uses to transition out of a cycle of busyness and into investing her time in the right things. Later in the episode, George chats with Daniel Ramsey, the executive vice president of EntreLeadership. Daniel talks about how to create healthy boundaries between work and your personal life. He also covers what it’s like to create boundaries in a family business—especially one where Dave Ramsey is your direct leader and your dad.


You’ll learn:

•      The real reason people stay so busy

•      If busy people are successful

•      If you’re getting the right things done every day

•      What to do if work is taking over your life
